l_main_2529744\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104luw1665702745876.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/luw1665702745876.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/luw1665702745876.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"luw1665702745876\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Standalone Cloud-Served License </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"luw1665702745876__cloud_served_standalone_license_202546\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A standalone cloud-served license is used for any Uniface application where the\n      license is locked to a machine, and connects to the Sentinel Cloud Server (SCC) to obtain and\n      periodically renew the lease on the license. This is also referred to as <dfn class=\"term\">lease\n         mode</dfn>. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luw1665702745876__p_d66953e1_d66954e1_d66955e1\">Cloud-served licensing requires an internet connection to activate the license and to periodically renew the lease on the license by connecting to the SCC. If the application has no internet connection, it can still continue to run as long as the lease period has not expired.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luw1665702745876__p_d66956e1_d66957e1_d66958e1\">For the Uniface 10\n         Community Edition, only standalone cloud-served licenses are used. For more information on\n         how to activate your license for the Community Edition, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zoh1665702745727.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zoh1665702745727.html\" title=\"The Uniface 10 Community Edition is a free version of Uniface that enables new and experienced developers, and others interested in Uniface 10 to explore, learn, and use Uniface 10 to build and test applications.\">Install the Uniface Community Edition</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luw1665702745876__p_d66959e1_d66960e1_d66961e1\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"luw1665702745876__p_d66962e1_d66963e1_d66964e1\">For the Enterprise Edition:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"luw1665702745876__li_d29582e1_d29583e1_d29584e1\">To configure a standalone cloud-served license, see\n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ltp1665702745946.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ltp1665702745946.html\" title=\"To configure a standalone cloud-served license, you need to enter your entitlement ID during installation or run the License Activation utility (ulic) after installing Uniface.\">Configuring Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"luw1665702745876__li_d29585e1_d29586e1_d29587e1\">To return a standalone cloud-served license, see\n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cgp1665702746819.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgp1665702746819.html\" title=\"You may wish to return a standalone cloud-served license on one machine to use it on another machine.\">Returning Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"luw1665702745876__li_d29588e1_d29589e1_d29590e1\">To update a standalone cloud-served license, see\n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"syz1665702746948.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/syz1665702746948.html\" title=\"If there are updates to the Entitlement for your standalone cloud-served license, for example adding or removing features, or extending the end date of the license, these will not take effect the first time you start your Uniface application.\">Updating Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses</a>. </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"luw1665702745876__note_w2613ab1b5c13_w2614ab1b5_w2615ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> \n                 For the Enterprise Edition, cloud-served licensing is only possible on Windows and Linux.</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529744\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529744\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Standalone Cloud-Served License Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Standalone Cloud-Served License A standalone cloud-served license is used for any Uniface application where the license is locked to a machine, and connects to the Sentinel Cloud Server (SCC) to obtain and periodically renew the lease on the license. This is also referred to as lease mode . Cloud-served licensing requires an internet connection to activate the license and to periodically renew the lease on the license by connecting to the SCC. If the application has no internet connection, it can still continue to run as long as the lease period has not expired. For the Uniface 10 Community Edition, only standalone cloud-served licenses are used. For more information on how to activate your license for the Community Edition, see Install the Uniface Community Edition . For the Enterprise Edition: To configure a standalone cloud-served license, see Configuring Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses . To return a standalone cloud-served license, see Returning Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses . To update a standalone cloud-served license, see Updating Standalone Cloud-Served Licenses . Note: For the Enterprise Edition, cloud-served licensing is only possible on Windows and Linux. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}